Job description:

Join us as a Pioneer and Strategic Builder in AI Innovation!

Australian Unity is embarking on a major transformation, shifting from traditional automation toward an intelligent, AI-powered future. We're looking for a Senior AI Automation Engineer to help shape this next generation of automation: one where AI Agents, large language models (LLMs), and modern frameworks transform how we work and deliver value to our customers.

In this hands on and strategic role, you'll play a key part in modernising our automation ecosystem; maintaining and enhancing current platforms (Appian, UiPath, Power Automate) while designing and implementing cutting-edge, AI-driven automation ecosystem. You'll combine deep technical expertise with creative problem solving, using first principles thinking to challenge the status quo, simplify complexity, and drive enterprise-wide efficiency.

This is a unique opportunity to lead the transition from classical RPA to AI-centric automation, setting the foundation for an adaptive, scalable, and future-ready technology landscape.

What You'll Do

¬∑ Lead end-to-end automation delivery, from concept to deployment.

¬∑ Modernise existing Automation ecosystem while building the foundations for AI Agent driven automation.

¬∑ Design and implement next generation automation using Generative AI, MCP Servers, and agent frameworks, extending the boundaries of what automation can do.

¬∑ Define and embed best practice design patterns, reusable modules, and delivery frameworks that improve speed, scalability, and governance.

¬∑ Monitor and optimise automation performance and outcomes to ensure business impact and alignment with strategic goals.

¬∑ Maintain and enhance current automation pipelines (Appian, UiPath, Power Automate), ensuring stability as we evolve the stack.

¬∑ Collaborate across business and technology teams to translate complex problems into practical, measurable automation solutions.

¬∑ Mentor and guide junior and offshore engineers, fostering a culture of innovation and technical excellence.

¬∑ Stay ahead of emerging technologies in AI, automation, and machine learning and bring fresh ideas that keep us at the forefront of innovation.

About You

We are looking for an innovator who's curious, forward-thinking, and thrives on solving complex challenges. You will bring a mix of hands-on technical skill and architectural vision. You question legacy approaches, design from first principles, and are excited by the possibilities of AI and automation convergence.

We also value an entrepreneur's mindset - someone who can wear multiple hats, adapt fluidly to new challenges, and take on roles beyond coding to deliver meaningful business impact. Start-up or similar experience that demonstrates versatility, ownership, and comfort operating in a fast-changing environment - whether as a founder or an early employee - will be highly regarded.

You will have:

¬∑ Degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field 5+ years commercial experience with at least 2 years in a relevant technical or architect capacity

¬∑ Proven track record delivering complex AI/ML solutions

You'll have hands-on experience with:

¬∑ Generative AI & agentic frameworks (LangChain, LangGraph, AutoGen, MCP Servers, etc.)

¬∑ Proficiency in at least one programming language (preferably Python), with strong OOP and design-pattern skills, and the ability to deliver high-quality, well-tested code.

¬∑ Excellent problem-solving skills and ability to translate business needs into technical solutions.

¬∑ Deep technical / theoretical knowledge in at least one of the following sub-fields of AI: Machine Learning, Deep Learning, or Foundation Models

¬∑ Ability to collaborate with stakeholders and communicate technical concepts clearly ¬∑ Technology/AI architecture, governance, responsible AI frameworks and scalability in enterprise environments

¬∑ Familiarity with RPA/BPA platforms such as UiPath, Appian, and Power Automate or strong willingness to learn.

What's on Offer:

You will enjoy a range of great employee benefits and rewards including:

¬∑ Competitive salary + bonus program

¬∑ Enjoy additional yearly Well-Being and Community leave days

¬∑ 14-week paid parental leave, with equal benefit for both parents

¬∑ Employee Referral Program

¬∑ Employee Assistance Program - support and assistance for you and your partner at those times in life when you need it most

¬∑ Maxxia Rewards - a great range of discounts and benefits at selected retail outlets, department stores, attractions, travel, cinemas, restaurants.

¬∑ Discounts across the Australian Unity business including Private Health Insurance, General Insurance + more!

¬∑ Available access to LinkedIn Learning courses through our great Learning platform.

For further benefits visit: https://www.australianunity.com.au/careers/culture

Australian Unity is an Equal Opportunity employer and we encourage applications from all members of the community, including people of Aboriginal and Torres strait Islander descent, culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds and, mature aged people.

Principal Enterprise Architect - Data & Knowledge

TechnologyOne is on a mission to transform how enterprise software is architected and delivered. As the Principal Enterprise Architect - Data & Knowledge, you will design and lead the modern data and knowledge architecture underpinning TechnologyOne's Data & AI Platform. You will establish the platform's unified data models, semantic foundations, vector-based retrieval pipelines, and industry-ready ontologies - enabling trusted, context-aware, AI-led operations across all products.

What you'll be doing‚Ä¶

1. Lead the Data Foundation Architecture





Architect modern lakehouse and data-fabric patterns using Snowflake, Databricks, Palantir, and AWS native services.
Define unified metadata, lineage, quality, and interoperability frameworks.
Design reusable data products for internal teams, customers, and marketplace developers.
Drive scalable ingestion for structured, unstructured, streaming, and synthetic data.
Ensure strong data management and governance aligned to platform standards.

2. Build the Enterprise Knowledge & Context Layer





Design semantic models, ontologies, and canonical entities used across domains.
Develop and maintain knowledge graphs (e.g., Neo4j, AWS Neptune).
Lead architecture for vector stores, RAG pipelines, embeddings, and chunking strategies (Pinecone, Weaviate, pgvector, ES vector).
Create the semantic and contextual grounding needed for AI assistants, agents, and analytics.

3. Enable AI, Agents & Intelligent Workflows





Integrate data and knowledge layers into AI orchestration, tool use, memory, and agent frameworks.
Collaborate with AI engineering on LLM/SLM switchboards, retrieval, grounding, and evaluation.
Support development of cross-module intelligent workflows for Finance, HR, Asset, Student, and platform-level agents.
Ensure reliability, observability, and explainability of AI features through strong context and data governance.

4. Governance, Quality & Trust by Design





Embed policy, lineage, and model/data governance across pipelines.
Implement standards for accuracy, explainability, auditability, and risk controls.
Partner with compliance and product teams to ensure platform-wide data and AI trust.

5. Leadership, Influence & Technical Excellence





Mentor engineers, data scientists, and architects.
Set technical direction, patterns, and reference architectures.
Work with product and industry teams to define workflow-aligned ontologies and data/knowledge products.
Champion modern data engineering, semantic modelling, and AI-driven design across the organisation.

Your Talents‚Ä¶





Deep practitioner experience with modern data platforms:
Snowflake, Databricks, Palantir, Lakehouse, data fabric patterns.
Hands-on technical expertise with metadata, governance, lineage, and data quality systems.
Strong architecture experience with knowledge graphs, ontologies, semantic models.
Practical experience designing vector search, embeddings, chunking, RAG pipelines.
Excellent understanding of cloud-native services, especially AWS (Redshift, Glue, Neptune, Sagemaker, Step Functions, Lambda, Bedrock/Anthropic models).
Experience working with or building agentic AI systems, retrieval grounding, or multi-agent orchestration.
Ability to translate complex architectures into clear platform roadmaps.
A builder mindset - comfortable designing, prototyping, and guiding engineering execution.

TechnologyOne is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer who values diversity and an inclusive workplace. We aim to recruit a diverse range of people with a diverse range of talents to help us deliver on our mission to better our community. Our core values and culture unleash the boundless potential of creativity, innovation and the entrepreneurial spirit within our people. Who we are‚Ä¶

At TechnologyOne (ASX: TNE), we're more than Australia's largest top 50 ASX enterprise SaaS company; we're a team driven by purpose! Our global SaaS ERP solution powers over 1,300 leading organisations, including government, education, health, and financial services. We take full responsibility for delivering outcomes - reducing time, cost, and risk; therefore, our customers can focus on what matters most. For over 38 years, we've been helping communities and organisations thrive by making life simple through innovative technology. Ready to make a real difference? Join us and help shape the future of enterprise technology while building a career that matters.

Location: Melton
Duration: 6-month contract opportunity
Hybrid work arrangement

About the role:
Our client is looking for an Azure Integration Developer to contribute to the design, development, implementation, and ongoing support of integration
solutions across a diverse suite of enterprise applications, ensuring reliable and secure data exchange across the organisation.¬† This is a hands-on development role with a strong focus on Microsoft Azure services, API management, and infrastructure.

Key responsibilities:

Lead the planning, design, and development of integration solutions using Azure Integration Services (Function Apps, Logic Apps, API Management, CI/CD) and TechnologyOne tools (T1 Connect, REST APIs, Data Exchange, Ci Anywhere).
Provide guidance on integration best practices, technical approaches, and solution design.
Collaborate with business analysts, project teams, architects, and stakeholders to translate requirements into scalable integration solutions aligned with organisational objectives.
Develop and maintain integration workflows, APIs, and scripts in line with architecture patterns, governance, security, and compliance standards.
Maintain clear documentation including designs, mappings, configurations, and test artefacts.
Required skills and experience:

Expertise in designing and implementing integration platforms using Azure Integration Services (APIM, Logic Apps, Service Bus/Queue, Data Factory, Functions, Storage).
Strong skills in API design and development aligned with RESTful standards (Swagger/OpenAPI), versioning, security, and performance optimisation.
Proficiency with Azure DevOps CI/CD pipelines.
Experience integrating IaaS, PaaS, and SaaS applications for seamless data exchange.
Ability to apply theoretical and analytical methods to solve complex or unfamiliar problems.
Understanding of Council‚Äôs long‚Äëterm goals, values, and operating context.
